      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Private ¶ 19. 5. [189]3 ¶ editorial addition. ¶ Dear Baron von Mueller, ¶  ¶ Permit me to thank you very cordially for your exceedingly kind notes received a few days ago. ¶ Notes not found. ¶  ¶ I am...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">93.05.19</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From James Thomson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">OM 65-21/1, letterbook of James Park Thomson, pp. 314-5, John Oxley Library, State Library of Queensland, Brisbane.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Private</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">19. 5. [189]3<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Permit me to thank you very cordially for your exceedingly kind notes received a few days ago.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Notes not found.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I am now drawing Mr. Healey's<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Not identified.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>attention to the subject you speak of. I am looking forward with much pleasure to your promised letter on New Guinea [… …]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The paper has become extremely friable and much of the centre of the MS sheet has crumbled away. All [… …] in the text below have this meaning.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>most honoured by your appreciation [… …] attentions to you. It is [… …] I take much delight in [… …] [tr]ust I may found my opini[on] [… …] permitted to offer my humble resp[ects] to one for whom I entertain the deepest r[es]pect &amp; who has done more to further scientific pursuits in Australasia than any [o]ther living man.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I see Mr. H. O. [Forbes] [… …] every opportunity of showing his [… …] to Sir William MacGregor &amp; [… …] I am amazed to think the Royal Geographical Society of London could not have found a more suitable &amp; worthy subject upon which to bestow its Gold Medal. An act of this kind brings Geography &amp; exploration into contempt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>The Royal Geographical Society awarded<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Henry<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Forbes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1893 Gill Memorial (not<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a gold<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>medal<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as reported in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Brisbane<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">c</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">ourier</seg>, 29 April 1893, p. 5) for his 'explorations in New Guinea, the Malay Archipelago, and the Chatham Islands' (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Geographical<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">j</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">ournal</seg>, vol. 1, p. 452).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The Gill memorial is listed elsewhere as among the awards carrying a premium.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Balance sheet for the 1893 year shows<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Gill Memorial'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>capital fund earned £35/1/10 in dividends, but it is not clear whether all of this was given to Forbes.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Forbes had been<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>supported by the Royal Geographical Society and other UK bodies to explore British New Guinea<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see M to W. Sewell, 23 October 1885). He arrived in 1885<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>began exploration but ran out of funds. He<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sought<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>additional funds and received support from the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(RGSA)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but still failed to complete his expedition. 'The scant results from Forbes's well-publicized activities<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>…<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>seriously damaged his reputation in Australia … [and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>his map] was later declared completely unreliable' (ADB).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>There are many letters between M and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Forbes, and between M and others concerning the expedition and the fate of the specimens. See, for example,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to J. Chalmers, 18 May 1886 (in this edition as 86-05-18a)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and notes thereto;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M. to H. Ridley, 21 September 1886;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 17 August 1887 (in this edition as 87-08-17c); H. Forbes to M, 5 September 1887 (in this edition as 87-09-05a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See also Forbes's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>letters to the press,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>6 May 1887, p. 9<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>16 May 1887,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 7, the latter in response to the report of the meeting of the Council of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Victorian Branch<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>RGSA at which Forbes's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>first letter<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was discussed (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 12 May 1887, p. 9). There is a relevant letter of Frederick McCoy to the editor of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 17 June 1887, p. 10.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Those who do good honest &amp; valuable work are overlooked.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are in a state of very great excitement here just now. I trust it will soon be quiet again.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With kind regards,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>dear Baron von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>very faithfully yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. P. Thomson</p>
         </div>
      </body>
